        {
            "text": "Summary",
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "A search for solar axions with a 59.5 day exposure of 106 kg NaI(Tl) in the COSINE-100 dark matter search experiment has been performed. ",
            "section": "Summary",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "Here we apply the recent prediction for the solar axion flux that assumes that axions produce electron recoil signals in the NaI(Tl) detector through the axio-electric effects. ",
            "section": "Summary",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "There is no excess of events that could be attributed to solar axion interactions and we determined a 90% CL limit of the axion-electron coupling, g ae < 1.70 \u00d7 10 \u221211 for m a = 0 keV to 1 keV. ",
            "section": "Summary",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 106,
                    "end": 108,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CL",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w9"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "This excludes QCD axions heavier than 0.59 eV/c 2 in the DFSZ model and 168.1 eV/c 2 in the KSVZ model.",
            "section": "Summary",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
